United Technologies Boosts Forecasts After Profit Gains 19%

-- B y   R a c h e l   L a y n e
-- 
2011-07-20T11:50:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/united-technologies-boosts-forecasts-after-profit-gains-19-.html
United Technologies Corp. (UTX)  boosted
its sales and earnings forecasts for the year after second-
quarter profit topped analystsâ€™ estimates amid gains in the
Carrier air-conditioning division.  Sales in 2011 may be $58 billion, compared with a previous
forecast of at least $57 billion, the Hartford, Connecticut-
based company said today in a statement. Full-year profit will
be higher than previously forecast at $5.35 to $5.45 a share,
the company said.  Second-quarter net income rose to $1.32 billion, or $1.45 a
share, from, $1.11 billion, or $1.20 a year earlier, the
Hartford, Connecticut-based company said. That surpassed the
$1.42 average estimate from 19 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.
Sales climbed 9.2 percent to $15.1 billion, higher than the
average estimate of $14.7 billion. 